cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper deals with hyperspectral image classification using a convolutional neural network and Markov random fields. The most relevant sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper focuses on image classification. The use of a CNN also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.LG (Machine Learning), as CNNs are a popular machine learning technique. The Bayesian framework used in the paper also suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Markov random fields and the iterative update process suggest the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
